# CSS Nesting And Specificity

- Prefer nested CSS for both organization and specificity.
- Scope overrides through the existing component root selector first.
- Do not create long one-off class names just to force specificity.
- Add a new class only when it represents a real semantic or reusable element, not a specificity workaround.
- When styling component children inside a nested root, prefer terse underscore-prefixed child selectors like `._panel` or `._day`.
- Use longer non-underscored class names only when the selector must work outside the component root, such as with intentionally portaled content.

## Preferred

```css
.profile-drawer {
  ._trigger {
    position: absolute;
  }

  ._content {
    z-index: 140;
  }
}
```

## Avoid

```css
.profile-drawer-avatar-regenerate-trigger {
  position: absolute;
}

.profile-drawer-avatar-tooltip {
  z-index: 140;
}
```
